Rd1 ({A direct assault on the a-file brings nothing:} 21. Qa6 Qc7 22. Ra1 Rb8 {
[%cal Gb8b6]}) 21... Qa5 {This interesting manoeuvre by Black's queen seems to
keep the balance, since neither taking on d6, nor exchanging queens on a5
promise White anything.  However, White still has a formal edge thanks to the
weak pawns on d6 and b4, but he needs to find more resources to keep up the
pressure.} 22. h5 $1 {Morozevich skillfully creates problems by playing on
both wings. Now Black faces a rather unpleasant choice: to go for a
dangerous-looking endgame by handing White the control over the a-file, or
